<HEADLINE> Colombia Army Col. Assassinated  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) -- Gunmen assassinated an off-duty
Colombian army colonel as he watched a children's beauty contest
with his wife and 10-year-old daughter, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Two hit men walked into the event Saturday night in Rivera, a
small town in southern Huila state, shot Col. Oscar Trujillo two
times in the head, and then fled on a motorcycle.
</P>
<P>
   Huila, where Trujillo was gunned down, has been the scene of
fierce attacks in recent days by Colombia's largest leftist
insurgency, the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia, or FARC.
</P>
<P>
   The officer was on vacation, hundreds of miles from where he is
stationed. Trujillo commands an army battalion in the violent
northern banana-growing region known as Uraba, an area teeming with
leftist rebels and rival rightist paramilitary groups.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said they had no hard leads yet into who killed
Trujillo. But the regional army commander, Gen. Carlos Ospina of
the army's Fourth Division, said he suspected the FARC urban
commandoes active in Huila. The group has assassinated high-ranking
military officers in the past.
</P>
</TEXT>
