<HEADLINE> Turkish TV Host Koray Dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANKARA, Turkey (AP) -- Cenk Koray, a Turkish television host and
journalist, died Sunday of a heart attack in his Istanbul home,
news reports said. He was 56.
</P>
<P>
   Koray amused Turkish TV audiences during much of the 1970s and
1980s with his wit and humor as host of entertainment and game
shows.
</P>
<P>
   Born in Adana, southern Turkey, in 1944, Koray trained as a
lawyer but chose journalism as a career instead. His lucky break
came when he was asked to stand in for another popular TV presenter
who was on vacation.
</P>
<P>
   For the past few years, Koray had been writing a column for the
daily newspaper Aksam and was the spokesman for his favorite soccer
team, Istanbul's Besiktas, until last season.
</P>
<P>
   Koray is survived by a sister.
</P>
</TEXT>
