<HEADLINE> Suspicious Man Tries Visiting Model  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MADRID, Spain (AP) -- Claudia Schiffer got a visit from a man
carrying a large bouquet of flowers, but he wasn't at the
supermodel's doorstep for a date.
</P>
<P>
   Police said a 44-year-old man who was fleeing an arrest warrant
for assault and battery approached a patrolman, identified himself
as Schiffer's husband and asked for directions to her summer home
in Spain, the state news agency Efe reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The officer gave him directions but called his base to report
his suspicions. Police detained the man as he knocked on the door --
with flowers in hand, the agency reported.
</P>
<P>
   Schiffer was not in the residence at the time.
</P>
</TEXT>
