<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-23 18:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police say convicted felon assaulted children, stored weapons in home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CORNWALL, N.Y. (AP) - A three-time convicted felon was charged
with handcuffing his 15-year-old son to a pole and beating him with
a leather belt and a pool stick.
</P>
<P>
   The father, John Vachaviolas, was arrested Saturday after the
boy escaped through a second-story window, ran to a convenience
store and called for help, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Detective Philip Sinagra said Vachaviolas, 40, is a three-time
convicted felon. After his arrest, police found two assault rifles,
18 assorted shotguns and a handgun in the house. As a prior
convicted felon, Vachaviolas is prohibited from possessing
firearms.
</P>
<P>
   Sinagra said two other children were also assaulted and locked
in their bedrooms.
</P>
<P>
   Since Jan. 1, police say they have been to the Vachaviolas home
eight times for situations between the father and his four
children.
</P>
<P>
   The father is the only parent in the house, Sinagra said.
</P>
<P>
   The children were treated at a hospital and released. They were
in the custody of Child Protective Services and will be placed in
temporary foster care.
</P>
<P>
   Vachaviolas was arraigned and sent to Orange County Jail without
bail. His home phone number was non-published and a message left
for him at the jail was not immediately returned.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
