<HEADLINE> 20 Illegal Immigrants Held in USVI  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Police have
detained 20 illegal Chinese immigrants who were dropped off by boat
in the U.S. Virgin Islands, but around 20 others on the boat eluded
authorities.
</P>
<P>
   A citizen rounded up 20 Chinese nationals and one Haitian man
and put them in his truck to take them to the police station, but
the Haitian jumped out of the truck and escaped, said police Sgt.
Annette Raimer.
</P>
<P>
   Police said as many as 40 people were on the boat that let off
the illegal immigrants on St. Thomas' north coast Saturday, and
police were searching for the passengers who fled.
</P>
<P>
   So far this year, 346 Chinese have been detained for illegally
entering the United States through the Caribbean territory, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Immigration officials have said that many of the migrants pay
thousands of dollars to smuggling rings that move them through
other Caribbean islands on their way to the Virgin Islands to
arrive on U.S. soil.
</P>
</TEXT>
