<HEADLINE> State police investigator charged with drunk driving  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ONEIDA, N.Y. (AP) - A state police investigator was charged
Friday with driving while intoxicated, state police said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigator Lyndy Helt was charged after a crash a few minutes
after midnight in Oneida, Maj. James Parmley said. No one was hurt.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's embarrassing, obviously, to the state police,'' Parmley
said. ''She's facing disciplinary action. She has a clean record,
and she was in her own car at the time.''
</P>
<P>
   Helt, who is on vacation, will be placed on administrative duty
and relieved of her caseload when she returns, Parmley said. AN
internal investigation will be conducted. State Police
Superintendent James McMahon ultimately will decide her punishment.
</P>
<P>
   Details of the crash were unavailable.
</P>
<P>
   There was no phone listing for Helt.
</P>
