<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON HEIGHTS, Ill. (AP) -- Pine Dance beat Hymn by 1&AMP;frac12;
lengths Sunday to win the $200,000 American Derby at Arlington
International Racecourse.
</P>
<P>
   The European-based Pine Dance, ridden by Eddie Ahern, took the
lead for good in the field of four at the top of the stretch and
finished 1 3-16 miles on the turf in 1:55.46.
</P>
