<HEADLINE> Devers Beats Own 100 Hurdles Record  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Gail Devers, who nearly quit track
about 10 years ago because of Graves' Disease, shattered her
American record in the 100-meter hurdles Sunday night with a time
of 12.33 seconds at the U.S. Olympic trials.
</P>
<P>
   Devers, 33, broke the mark of 12.37 she set in winning her third
straight world title at Seville, Spain, last year.
</P>
<P>
   Devers also has two gold medals in the 100-meter dash at the
Olympic Games, but didn't make that team this year, finishing fifth
in the trials.
</P>
<P>
   The world record in the hurdles is 12.21 by Yordanka Donkova of
Bulgaria.
</P>
