<HEADLINE> Lynx 80, Fire 63  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Betty Lennox scored 26 points as the
Minnesota Lynx snapped a franchise-long eight-game losing streak
Sunday with an 80-63 victory over the Portland Fire.
</P>
<P>
   Marla Brumfield scored a career-high 14 points for the Lynx
(11-13), who hadn't lost more than four straight before this
season. Minnesota's last victory was July 2, when the Lynx beat
Portland 81-75.
</P>
<P>
   Stacey Thomas had a career-high 14 points and seven rebounds for
Portland (7-16), which has lost three in a row. Sophia Witherspoon
added 12 points.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota started the second half with a 24-12 run, sparked by
Shanele Stires' two 3-pointers. Katie Smith's only field goal, a
3-pointer with 9:45 left, gave the Lynx a 55-43 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Portland did not get closer than four points the rest of the
game.
</P>
<P>
   Brumfield shot 5-for-5 from the field and 4-for-4 from the foul
line. Smith, Minnesota's leading scorer, was 1-for-11 from the
field.
</P>
<P>
   The Lynx scored 23 points off 23 Portland turnovers, while the
Fire scored 24 off 21 Minnesota turnovers.
</P>
<P>
   The game was tied 31-31 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota won the season series 2-1.
</P>
</TEXT>
