<HEADLINE> Ben Crane Wins Wichita Open  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Ben Crane became the 12th Monday qualifier
to win a Buy.com Tour event, closing with a 5-under-par 67 on
Sunday for a three-stroke victory in the Wichita Open.
</P>
<P>
   Crane, who earned $72,000, had a 25-under 263 total on the
Willowbend Golf Club course to break the tournament record of 265
set by Emlyn Aubrey in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   The former University of Oregon player's 25-under total is the
second lowest in tour history, one shy of the mark set by Chris
Smith in the 1997 Omaha Classic.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm still a little numb. What an amazing week,'' said Crane,
who earned a full exemption for the rest of this year along with
the 2001 campaign if he does not advance to the PGA Tour.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm so thankful I can take Mondays off because they are so
tough. That's all I wanted, a place to play.''
</P>
<P>
   Kelly Grunewald and Vance Veazey closed with 65s to tie for
second at 266, and Richard Johnson (68) and Pat Perez (69) followed
at 267.
</P>
</TEXT>
