</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- George W. Bush's top vice presidential candidate, former
Defense Secretary Dick Cheney, has told associates there is a good chance he
will get the job, officials said today as the Republican governor from Texas
prepared to announce his pick. Cheney, former Sen. John Danforth of Missouri and
perhaps others are on Bush's short list, according to highly placed GOP
officials. In seclusion at his Texas ranch, Bush tentatively planned to
introduce his running mate Tuesday. Even his closest advisers said they did not
know if he had made up his mind Sunday.
</P>
